A convention for who yields the right-of-way does not imply any greater
or lesser right to use the road; it simply provides a mechanism for
allowing both kids' play and traffic flow to proceed.  Kids are supposed
to yield not because they have fewer rights, but rather, because kids
tend to stay in the same area while motorists tend to want to get
somewhere else. Whoever needs to get somewhere else will need a path
along which he can travel.  This has everything to do with common sense
and nothing to do with &quot;rights&quot;.
